<br>
I am Lvl 57 now and thought all my way this level up about weapons, damage/delay, DPS and how dual wield works. And in result of this im really not thinking of doing my epics....<br>
Let me just say, sure, these weapons are great for those who solo much, but for me personally these weapons make no sense.<br>
Lets take a look at the damage/delay stats on those:<br>
Primary: 14dmg 24dly<br>
Secondary: 13dmg 21dly (plz correct me if im false)<br>
<br>
Well, Earthcaller...... cough .... come on, 14 24???? The damage delay really sucks on this. There are a LOT of weapons you can get really easy or can buy with money, that are way!!! better than this. Personally for me im using a 12/20 weapon atm. Sure, its not an uber weapon, but the DPS is better than on Earthcaller. <br>
So, i would NEVER use Earthcaller while grouping in the Planes for example. Especially the proc is only a big aggro drawer.<br>
The slow proc makes it a good solo weapon though. But after the slow proced i would switch back to my better DPS weapon.<br>
<br>
Ok, Swiftwind....hmmm. î really thought long, long nights over this weapon and if i really should get it.<br>
Some people told me, come on Deecey, this weapon has 40% haste, you must get it.<br>
Well, ok, 40% haste is really much, but i personally gave it up to solo 90% of the time. I switched that, now im grouping 90% of my time and because of this there is mostly a high level chanter that hastes me up to the skill cap with his spell adding to my item haste. So it doesnt really matter now, if i have 22% or 40% haste unbuffed. So the haste is again only a good solo effect. No use for raids or grouping with a good balanced group.<br>
And about the damage delay. 13/21 isn´t really good stats for an offhand weapon, what i found out about the way dual wield is working.<br>
Now comes the part where im not really sure, if you found out something different or you are sure it works different please correct me here!!!<br>
In my eyes i found out, that the check for the offhand attack only happens after your primary attacked. If you ever wondered about, why Swiftwind is faster than Earthcaller, this is the reason. EC has a delay of 24, that means EC attacks every 2,4 secs without haste. SW has dly 21, that means it would attack evey 2,1 secs if you would wear it in primary. But SW is an offhand weapon, and offhand weapons have always to wait till the primary weapon attacked. So EC and SW would attack every 2,4 secs. In fact, the dly of Swiftwind could also be 15 or even lower, it would only attack after 2,4 secs because it has to wait for the primarys attack.<br>
 I tried out this theory with switching my weapons. Im using a 12/20 piercer in primary and 22/34 slashing in offhand. I switched the slower weapon to primary and so the faster weapon was in offhand. I noticed that my piercer attacked much lesser than before in primary. And that is now the point where im not sure anymore. Did it attack slower or lesser because it had to wait 3,4 secs for the primary or was it because my character failed the dual wield (at 230 now i guess) check a lot of times?!?<br>
Because of this lack of knowledge im using a hard hitting but slow weapon in offhand, it only attacks every second turn after my primary, but does a lot of damage that makes it worth it.<br>
But, regardless if the first theory is right or the other one, 13/21 arent good stats for offhand, because you lack very often the dual wield check, attacking only every second or even third turn and so youre not making much damage with your offhand. I guess and i hope this will getting better when i reached lvl 60 and have higher dual wield skill then and after you got the AA Ability Ambidexterity. <br>
Because of this i would really appreciate feedback of some high end lvl rangers with this ability, for example, Tegamyen, Tressia, Lendien or someone else <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
Ok, the last thing, i really can´t say anything against it, are the extra stats on the epics. They are really very nice and can help a lot. But for me extra stats on weapons don´t count. Im looking for the best DPS combination and would never use the epics because they give me more hps for example.<br>
<br>
So, considering all this, in my eyes, the Ranger Epics are made for the lonely Ranger out there using his most time with soloing. There are not much better weapons out there if you want to solo much. <br>
(Sure there are, but not every Ranger is member of FE =P)<br>
<br>
So, plz give me feedback what you think about the Epics and if im missing anything in my theory, that could change my mind and feel free to gimme a tell in the game to discuss about that.<br>
So far, i belong with saying: I´m not planning in doing the Epics, because i have no need for them.<br>
<br>
Deecey Riverwind<br>
57th Outrider of Tunare<br>
<br>
P.S.: Plz don´t look at my grammar. My english really sucks 8(<br>
