So you are right, when they came out, they WERE great weapons.<br>
<br>
And Xanthias, you don´t have to say sorry with calling me lazy, if i would read this post i would really think the same about that person.<br>
But actually i have most parts of my epics already and i would have only one step left if i wouldn´t have rejected the Jade Reaver drop while we were doing the Epic Shaman Quest in CoM, cause there was a Druid who was already waiting a very long time for the Jade Reaver.<br>
So, i´m definately not lazy.<br>
And FYI, after Lauris E-Mail, which was a really long and very good one, i`m considering finishing at least Swiftwind. But that will definately NOT be my personal goal in this game.<br>
Hell, what is Verant thinking they are doing here???<br>
Sure, you are right, the Epics WERE THE UBER weapons in this game when they came out and it WAS the goal of my first ranger to get those. But now, after the latest expansions came out there are a LOT of weapons that are better than a 14/24 weapon and fairly easy to get. And in fact, i know a LOT of Rangers who do have Earthcaller, but not using it while grouping or raiding, cause 14/24 IS definately lousy nowadays! <br>
<br>
Ok, Swiftwind is hard to beat, 13/21 isn´t too bad, BUT should be a primary weapon in my eyes, and with the haste of 40% only beaten by the Tolans Longsword of the Glade.<br>
But in my eyes a offhand weapon has to have at least high damage, as long as you don´t have the ability Ambidextirety.<br>
I´m using one piercing and one slashing weapon. In this way i can see how often the Dual Wield check fails at Lvl57.<br>
I found out that you have about a 70% chance of using your offhand weapon at lvl 57. When i put my piercing weapon into offhand i suddenly read ..you slash... nearly as often as .. you pierce.. though my piercing weapon is nearly double as fast as my slashing weapon. <br>
So 13dmg is in my eyes not enough dmg, cause you are not hitting that often with it as you think.<br>
<br>
<br>
WHEN you all this now have read, what you apparently haven´t done with my first posting, you will see Xanthias, that i´m thinking a lot of DPS, or i wouldn´t waste my time here, about what i have found out about Dual Wielding and wouldn´t have wasted my time in using LOTS of several weapons, switching them from primary to offhand and back, just to find out, with which i would do the best damage per second. Hell, this wasn´t really fun. So, plz don´t call me lazy anymore.<br>
