<br>
Earthcall<br>
<br>
Slot Description <br>
2:  Decrease Attack Speed by 20% (L1) to 50% (L60) <br>
3:  Decrease Hitpoints by 20 per tick <br>
<br>
1 ticks @L1 to 2.5 mins @L50<br>
<br>
So Earthcall landing on a target is a 50 percent slow and 500 point DoT. (at level 60+)<br>
<br>
<br>
Just the other day in PoV, I was in an XP group where the Shammie and Chanter died due to a train...  I had to snare off the cleric (who had to DA) and start the parking to get it under control while the tank handled the unrootable one.   I swapped in the earthcaller and landed procs while fending them off in my running and rooting parking frenzy.  The cleric was not happy because the mob on the tank wasn't slowed, the slowers were dead, and mana was dumping pretty fast.  I slide in behind the mob after getting the others in control and one Earthcall proc and a couple of jolts later we had drastically turned the odds in our favor.  Swapped the Earthcaller out for my DPS weapon and went back to work, only swapping it back in when the proc wore off on the mob we were fighting.  This coupled with dumping Chloroblasts for healing between mobs taking some of the load off the cleric and giving the other group members more time between fights made all the difference.<br>
<br>
I will never regret going through the trouble of getting both my epics.  I feel it's the same thing with any ranger quest out there.  Ivy Etched?  I did 'em...  SSoM?  Did it...  Trueshot/Raincaller... Yeap.    Quest spell?  You betcha.    Orc Impaler?  Yes.  (the list goes on)  Only ones I haven't done are the VERY new ones (Trueshot Armor/Twlight Armor, etc.) because my gear is better than those atm.<br>
<br>
I guess it's just a matter of what you play the game for...  I play to be the most well-rounded Ranger I can be.  When I'm not raiding or helping someone, I'm questing or grinding AA... <br>
<br>
<br>
If you put the time into it to develop the core people who will be interested in helping you ... then I'd have to say getting your Swiftwind is a MUST.  Earthcaller is a luck of the draw thing on the Mini's not being a pain every time you go.<br>
<br>
<br>
No one can tell you the sense of completion you'll get when you finally have both epics.   It's just something you have to experience for yourself.<br>
