<br>
We asked for more information, you chose not to give it.  It's hard to believe that the rangers with swiftwind were not doing at least the same damage as you as long as they were equipped decently in their primary hand or you have top end swords yourself.   That's what doesn't add up.<br>
<br>
You specifically asked that someone like Tressia respond to this thread, she did and other experienced rangers did to, and you just blow off their opinion.  Why did you ask the question in the first place?  You've decided the epics are not worth your time, fine, no need to rub in what you perceive as the worthlessness of them to others.<br>
<br>
Simply put, the ranger epics are not the best weapons in the game, but they are very far from worthless, and I still contend their duration of usefulness exceeds many other classes epic and remains useful to rangers to this day.<br>
<br>
I am still proudly using mine.  Shopping for an Earthcaller replacement to use each in the correct situation, just as I pull out my windblade when its appropriate to use that.<br>
